    {
      "id": "ced2762a6ee5c446d57891177d07957529e75e69",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-28 10:04:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nLooks pretty reasonable. I guess there can't really be a test added for larger blocksize until after we have updated to the latest ZFS code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d990cb157c91787b44c4211ea8e455d8b88cf2a1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 192,
        "name": "Brian Behlendorf",
        "email": "behlendorf1@llnl.gov",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-01-28 17:17:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAdding a test case is an excellent idea!  And I don't think we need to wait for large block support to be merged on the ZFS side (although that should happen soon).  The test case can easily perform a check to determine if ZFS supports large blocks and if so enable them.  I'll look in to adding a test when I refresh the patch.\n\nI'd like to refresh this patch at least one more time anyway to improve the documentation.  And I'm sure there will be some additional review comments.  I mainly wanted to get it pushed to get a first round of testing in and get feedback.\n\nIt also looks like it conflicts with quite a few other changes.  It would be nice to be able to start merging some of those other patches which are ready to reduce conflicts.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
